Flashcard rules:
- Generate 3–6 cards covering different angles: definition, example recognition, analogy, common mistake avoidance
- Each card tests exactly one thing — no compound questions
- front_text is a question or cloze prompt; back_text is the direct answer
- Cards must be self-contained (no reference to "the text above")
- Assign a bloom_level: remember | understand | apply | analyze | evaluate | create

Multiple-choice question rules:
- Generate 3–5 questions
- Each question has exactly 4 answer choices; exactly one is correct
- Wrong answers must be plausible (exploit the listed common mistakes where possible)
- Questions must be self-contained

